Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index rose 11.78, or 0.1 percent, to 8,969.43,
the highest since Feb. 9. The benchmark gained 2.9 percent this
week, the most since Dec. 4.  Fubon Financial Holding Co. (2881 TT) climbed 1.2 percent
to NT$40.90, the highest since Dec. 19, 2001. The company denied
a report by the Commercial Times itâ€™s in merger talks with Jih
Sun Financial Holdings Co. (5820 TT), according to a statement
to the Taiwan stock exchange yesterday.  Jih Sun dropped 1.1 percent to NT$14.15 after it also
denied the newspaper report in an exchange statement yesterday.  MStar Semiconductor Inc. (3697 TT) advanced 1.5 percent to
NT$240, the biggest gain since April 7. Its board of directors
approved a cash dividend of NT$10 per share as well as a stock
dividend of 10 percent on 2010 earnings, the Hsinchu, Taiwan-
based company said in an exchange statement yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
